I’ve isolated the core reward paths. One bug is already concrete and exploitable: `claimEarned` pays rewards without checking maturity or whether that reward was already claimed, and `unstake` later pays the same reward again because the two functions use inconsistent state. I’m now tightening exact line references and checking whether any additional insolvency paths are independent enough to report separately.
